      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Stopping antibiotics early can allow surviving bacteria to multiply, leading to a more severe or chronic infection that may be harder to treat in the future. The side effects like nausea are common but are often temporary, whereas the long-term risk of drug-resistant infections is a much greater medical issue. Health experts consistently recommend completing the full course because it is the only way to guarantee the infection is fully cleared. Please discuss your concerns about side effects with your doctor, but do not stop the medication without their explicit instruction.",
